# Kernel C (eink_drm)

Full guide: `docs/CODING_STYLE.md` · Architecture: `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`

## Must follow

- Linux kernel coding style + SPDX `GPL-2.0-only` headers
- **Clean-room only** — never copy from `reference/linux-2019/` or Windows trees
- Names teach intent: `ite8951_wait_display_ready`, not `await_OK` / `send_ctrl`
- Wrap opcodes/registers in named constants and small functions
- Comments only for non-obvious protocol, hardware layout, or trade-offs — not narrating `i++`
- Structure: logical blocks separated by blank lines; early `return` on errors; `goto` cleanup OK
- `dev_dbg` / `dev_err` with context (what, where, ret)
- kernel-doc on exported structs/functions

## Avoid

- Mega-functions, cryptic abbreviations, obvious comments
- `/dev/eink0` text protocol in production code
- Includes or logic from `reference/` paths

## Example

```c
/* Good */
ret = ite8951_set_waveform(usb, EINK_WAVEFORM_GL16);
if (ret)
	return ret;

/* Bad */
ret = ite8951_usb_xfer(usb, 0xA9, 0x01010000, ...); /* set waveform */
```
